\f1\b\fs32 Cover letter\
\pard\pardeftab709\sl288\slmult1\sa140

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To Whom it May Concern:\
We believe we would benefit a great deal from being selected as participants in the Open Policy Network's Institute for Open Leadership. As fellows and contributors to this network, we think openly reflecting on the challenges and successes of open policy implementation for Greenpeace International's Media Library will be beneficial to other organizations who are struggling to get themselves on the right side of the open culture movement.\
Behind the curtain at Steve's over eight years at Greenpeace, he has been a constant voice for implementing open policies within our media asset library. He has worked to find ways to convince our global offices and photographer networks to assign Creative Common Licenses, and has celebrated small wins since the first implementation of a Creative Commons License in 2010. There is still much work to form the \'93perfect\'94 open source media library. In particular, we see a need to create a variety of policies for our complicated asset library and to placate certain editors and photographers who do not yet understand the value of open licenses. \
Steve's team has been negotiating within Greenpeace national and regional offices as these are the entities that provide Greenpeace with content for Greenpeace Media (http://photo.greenpeace.org). We are aware of the need for strategic community support around creating and applying open policies, and so we are hopeful that you will accept our application to attend the Institute for Open Leadership. \
We hope to utilize the Institute as a time to learn more about open policy and licensing, gain support from your experts in the development of a likely complicated strategy for the Greenpeace Media Library. We are looking forward to contributing our experiences working with hundreds of differently minded content creators.\
We are willing and eager to fulfill the responsibilities of this fellowship, but we\'92ll be honest in saying it\'92s the fellowship community that we\'92re most excited about. We know that interacting with the other fellows will provide a number of learning opportunities for us, and we think we have experience and insight to contribute to this conversation. \
In short if you have an open spot for another fellow, we\'92d love the opportunity.\
Sincerely,\
Steve Cairns & Laura Hilliger (on behalf of the Library Team at Greenpeace International)\
